{
  "doc_id": "10792",
  "text": "Investigation of an uncontrollable or inaccessible quantum system or quantum systems with a large number of degrees of freedom via some controllable quantum system is known as quantum simulation [CITATION_1] [2] [CITATION_2] . To this end, a wide variety of systems such as atoms in optical lattices, trapped ions, nuclear spins, superconducting circuits and photonic systems have been proposed as quantum simulators in different branches of physics such as condensed matter physics, high-energy physics, and cosmology [CITATION_3] .",
